I",<h1 id="solution--calculate-a--b3">Solution : Calculate (a + b)^3</h1>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>fn test() {
    let a = 2;
    let b = 2;
    let c = i32::pow(a,3) + i32::pow(b, 3) + ( 3 * a * b * (a + b)) ; 
    println!("{}",c);  
}

</code></pre></div></div>
<p>output</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>64

</code></pre></div></div>

<h1 id="explanation">Explanation</h1>

<ul>
  <li>On line 2, a variable a with value 2 is declared. <br /></li>
  <li>On line 3, a variable b with value 2 is declared. <br /></li>
  <li>
    <p>On line 4, addition takes place of : <br /></p>

    <ul>
      <li>a​3​​ ( calculated using the function pow)</li>
      <li>b​3​​ ( calculated using the function pow)</li>
      <li>3∗a∗b( multiplied with (a+b))(a + b))(a+b))</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>

